predictions.rationale: The student consistently solves linear-function tasks correctly, explains slope/intercepts conceptually, self-checks and generalizes the rise/run “step” method to new points with only minor confidence doubts.

After initial confusion and anxiety, the student correctly factors and solves several quadratics (including sign cases) with minimal prompting, but shows limited confidence and struggles to transfer the idea to leading coefficients/fractions.

The student uses precise thermodynamics vocabulary, anticipates key caveats (phase change, variable heat capacities), connects concepts across equipartition/entropy/real-gas effects, and independently proposes correct quantitative approximations (implicit differentiation, low-density limit, inversion temperature).
